<h2>📌 About This Project</h2>

<p>
The <b>Indian Voting System</b> is a modern web-based platform designed to provide a
secure, transparent and efficient way to conduct elections digitally. Traditional
voting methods often require significant manpower, physical resources and time.
This system aims to simplify the entire voting process by allowing voters to
participate through an online interface.
</p>

<p>
The platform enables administrators to create elections, manage candidates and
register voters while ensuring that the voting process remains fair and transparent.
Each registered voter can securely cast their vote using their voter credentials.
The system automatically counts votes and displays the results instantly,
reducing the chances of human error.
</p>

<p>
This project is built as part of an academic learning experience to demonstrate
the practical implementation of modern web technologies. It showcases how
digital systems can improve traditional processes and increase efficiency.
</p>

<p>
Technologies used in this project include:
</p>

<ul>
<li><b>Node.js & Express.js</b> for backend server development.</li>
<li><b>MongoDB</b> for secure database storage.</li>
<li><b>EJS Templates</b> for dynamic webpage rendering.</li>
<li><b>HTML, CSS and JavaScript</b> for creating a responsive and interactive user interface.</li>
</ul>

<p>
The system focuses on security, usability and performance to ensure that the
online voting process remains smooth and trustworthy.
</p>

</div>


<!-- Privacy Policy -->

<div class="card india-card">

<h2>🔒 Privacy Policy</h2>

<p>
The privacy of voters is one of the most important aspects of any voting system.
The Indian Voting System has been designed with strict privacy principles to
ensure that user data remains protected and confidential.
</p>

<p>
When a voter registers or logs into the system, certain information such as
name, voter ID and contact details may be required for verification purposes.
This information is used only to authenticate voters and prevent unauthorized
access to the voting platform.
</p>

<p>
The system follows several important privacy guidelines:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Personal information is stored securely in the database.</li>
<li>Voter identity is protected and cannot be linked to the vote they cast.</li>
<li>No sensitive user information is shared with third parties.</li>
<li>Data is used only for the purpose of maintaining election integrity.</li>
</ul>

<p>
The platform ensures that every vote remains confidential and that voters can
participate without worrying about privacy concerns. Protecting voter data and
maintaining election transparency are top priorities of this system.
</p>

</div>


<!-- Terms of Service -->

<div class="card india-card">

<h2>📜 Terms of Service</h2>

<p>
By accessing and using the Indian Voting System, users agree to comply with
the rules and guidelines established for fair and responsible participation.
These terms are designed to maintain the integrity and reliability of the
voting process.
</p>

<p>
The following terms apply to all users of the platform:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Each voter is allowed to vote only once during an election.</li>
<li>Users must provide accurate information during registration.</li>
<li>Unauthorized attempts to access the system are strictly prohibited.</li>
<li>Administrators are responsible for managing voters and candidates.</li>
<li>Any misuse of the system may result in restricted access.</li>
</ul>

<p>
The platform is intended primarily for educational, organizational or
demonstration purposes. The system demonstrates how technology can be used
to conduct elections efficiently and transparently in the digital era.
</p>

<p>
By continuing to use the system, users acknowledge and agree to follow
these terms and conditions.
</p>

